The paper deals with designing adaptive predictors and quantizers for time-varying multiuser MIMO systems, which involves concepts from information theory (IT), networking and internet architecture (NI), control systems (SY), multimedia (MM), and machine learning (LG). However, since the focus is primarily on signal processing and communication aspects, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories. The use of adaptive algorithms and recursive least squares also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). The mention of simulation results and bit error rate analysis indicates a possible link to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of differential quantization and modeling of Gaussian MIMO channels suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
